 modification, thereby conferring resistance to macrolides.'),(244,'ARO:3000202','Cfr 23S ribosomal RNA methyltransferase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000052,ARO:3000240,ARO:3000241,ARO:3000267,ARO:3000315,ARO:3004575','','Cfr genes produce enzymes which catalyze the methylation of the 23S rRNA subunit at position 8 of adenine-2503. Methylation of 23S rRNA at this site confers resistance to some classes of antibiotics, including streptogramins, chloramphenicols, florfenicols, linezolids and clindamycin.'),(245,'ARO:3000203','hydrolysis of beta-lactam antibiotic by metallo-beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000040','','Mechanism of enzymatic degradation common to Ambler Class B beta-lactamases. One or two zinc atoms are used to orient a hydroxide nucleophile for attack of the beta-lactam ring.  In contrast to serine beta-lactamases, no acyl-enzyme intermediate is formed.'),(246,'ARO:3000205','tetX','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000036','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000030,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000069,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000152,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000528,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000667,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000668,participates_in ARO:3000450','TetX is a flavin-dependent monooxygenase conferring resistance to tetracycline antibiotics. TetX hydroxylates position 11a of the tetraketide group thus inactivating the antibiotic.'),(247,'ARO:3000206','emrK','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000373','emrK is a membrane fusion protein that is a homolog of EmrA. Together with the inner membrane transporter EmrY and the outer membrane channel TolC, it mediates multidrug efflux.'),(248,'ARO:3000207','acrA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000384','Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrA represents the periplasmic portion of the transport protein.'),(249,'ARO:3000208','glycosylation of antibiotic conferring resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0001004','','Addition of glycosyl moiety to antibiotics thereby inactivating them.'),(250,'ARO:3000209','antibiotic resistant DNA topoisomerase subunit parY','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000370','derives_from ARO:3003258','ParY is part of a topoisomerase IV that is resistant to antibiotics that affect other topoisomerases.'),(251,'ARO:3000210','rifamycin-resistant beta-subunit of RNA polymerase (rpoB)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000381,ARO:3000383,ARO:3003276','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000157,derives_from ARO:3000737','Rifampin resistant RNA polymerases include amino acids substitutions which disrupt the affinity of rifampin for its binding site. These mutations are frequently concentrated in the rif I region of the beta-subunit and most often involve amino acids which make direct interactions with rifampin. However, mutations which also confer resistance can occur outside this region and may involve amino acids which do not directly make contact with rifampin.'),(252,'ARO:3000211','ribosomal alteration conferring antibiotic resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0001001','','Chemical alteration of the ribosome results in modification of an antibiotic`s target leading to resistance.'),(253,'ARO:3000212','mutation conferring antibiotic resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0001001','','Point mutations in the DNA may lead to an altered gene product that may result in antibiotic resistance. Examples included modified antibiotic targets with lower binding affinities and the deactivation of repressors that result in increased expression of genes that inactivate or pump out antibiotics.'),(254,'ARO:3000213','restructuring of bacterial cell wall conferring antibiotic resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0001001','','Peptidoglycan precursors ending in D-Ala-D-Lac or D-Ala-D-Ser instead of D-Ala-D-Ala conferring high level glycopeptide resistance.'),(255,'ARO:3000214','hygromycin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','Hygromycin B is an aminoglycoside antibiotic used to treat different types of bacterial infections. Hygromycin B works by binding to the bacterial 30S ribosomal subunit, causing misreading of mRNA and leaving the bacterium unable to synthesize proteins vital to its growth. Hygromycin B has also been shown to interact with eukaryotic cells.'),(256,'ARO:3000215','mecR1','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000100','part_of ARO:3000268,regulates ARO:3000617,regulates ARO:3001209','mecR1 is a transmembrane spanning and signal transducing protein which in response to interaction with beta-lactam antibiotics results in upregulation of the mecA/mecR1/mecI operon.'),(257,'ARO:3000216','acrB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000384','Protein subunit of AcrA-AcrB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrB functions as a herterotrimer which forms the inner membrane component and is primarily responsible for substrate recognition and energy transduction by acting as a drug/proton antiporter.'),(258,'ARO:3000217','blaR1','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000100','part_of ARO:3000262,regulates ARO:3000621','blaR1 is a transmembrane spanning and signal transducing protein which in response to interaction with beta-lactam antibiotics results in upregulation of the blaZ/blaR1/blaI operon.'),(259,'ARO:3000218','aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase (ANT)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000104,ARO:3000557','participates_in ARO:3000107','Covalent modification of aminoglycoside antibiotic hydroxyl group by ATP-dependent transfer of AMP.'),(260,'ARO:3000219','mutant efflux regulatory protein conferring antibiotic resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000031','','Efflux regulatory proteins with mutations that result in increased expression of efflux proteins.'),(261,'ARO:3000220','antibiotic resistant DNA topoisomerase subunit gyrB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000370','derives_from ARO:3000734','Point mutations in gyrB confer antibiotic resistance by preventing drugs from binding the beta-subunit of gyrase, essential for DNA supercoiling.'),(262,'ARO:3000221','lincosamide nucleotidyltransferase (LNU)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000241,ARO:3000557','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000017,participates_in ARO:3000107','Resistance to the lincosamide antibiotic by ATP-dependent modification of the 3` and/or 4`-hydroxyl groups of the methylthiolincosamide sugar.'),(263,'ARO:3000222','gramicidin A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000123','','Gramicidin A is the most abundant (more than 80%) of the three gramicidins in gramicidin D, with a tryptophan in position 11. Gramicidins form dimers in the bacterial membrane that increase the permeability of cations.'),(264,'ARO:3000223','gramicidin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000123','','Gramicidin B is one of the three gramicidins in gramicidin D, with a phenylalanine in position 11. It is structurally similar to gramicidin A, but its ability to induce the assembly of bilayers is reduced. Gramicidins form dimers in the bacterial membrane that increase the permeability of cations.'),(265,'ARO:3000224','gramicidin C','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000123','','Gramicidin C is one of the three gramicidins in gramicidin D, with a tyrosine in position 11. It is structurally similar to gramicidin A, but its ability to induce the assembly of bilayers is reduced. Gramicidins form dimers in the bacterial membrane that increase the permeability of cations.'),(266,'ARO:3000225','ANT(6)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000218','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000016','Nucelotidylylation of streptomycin at the hydroxyl group at position 6'),(267,'ARO:3000226','antibiotic resistant folP','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000031','derives_from ARO:3000744','Point mutations in dihydropteroate synthase folP prevent sulfonamide antibiotics from inhibiting its role in folate synthesis, thus conferring sulfonamide resistance.'),(268,'ARO:3000227','tyrothricin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000707','has_part ARO:3000123','Tyrothricin is a mixture of antibiotics including tyrocidines and gramicidins, isolated from Bacillus brevis.'),(269,'ARO:3000228','ANT(9)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000218','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000016','Nucleotidylylation of spectinomycin at the hydroxyl group at position 9'),(270,'ARO:3000229','ANT(4`)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000218','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000016,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000005,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000021,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000049,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000052,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000652,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000653,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000655,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000657,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000700,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000701','Nucleotidylylation of 2-deoxystreptamine aminoglycosides at the hydroxyl group at position 4`'),(271,'ARO:3000230','ANT(2``)-Ia','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004276','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000014,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000049,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000052,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000655,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3003675','Plasmid or integron-encoded nucleotidylylation of 2-deoxystreptamine aminoglycosides at the hydroxyl group at position 2`` in P. aeruginosa, K. pneumoniae, Morganella morganii, E. coli, S. typhimurium, C. freundii and A. baumannii'),(272,'ARO:3000231','beta-lactam resistance operon','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000010','','An operon conferring resistance to beta-lactam antibiotics.'),(273,'ARO:3000232','ANT(3``)-Ia','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004275','','Nucleotidylylation of streptomycin at the hydroxyl group at position 3``'),(274,'ARO:3000233','streptogramin inactivation enzyme','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000240,ARO:3000557','','Resistance to streptogramin antibiotics may be conferred through enzymatic inactivation. There are two known mechanisms of streptogramin inactivation shown clinically to confer resistance: 1) vgB lyase enzymes linearize type B streptogramin antibiotics by breaking the ester linkage; 2) vat acetyltransferase enzymes modify type A streptogramin antibiotics by transferring an acetyl group from acetyl-CoA to the secondary streptogramin hydroxyl. Both mechanisms result in antibiotic inactivation thus conferring resistance.'),(275,'ARO:3000234','glycopeptide resistance gene cluster','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000010','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000081,participates_in ARO:3000213','Genes that when expressed confer resistance to vancomycin and teicoplanin type antibiotics.'),(276,'ARO:3000235','ethambutol resistant embB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3002876','derives_from ARO:3000765','embB gene encodes for an arabinosyl transferase in the arabinogalactan synthesis pathway. It is inhibited by ethambutol. Mutations within the ERDR region of embB confers resistance to ethambutol.'),(277,'ARO:3000236','glycopeptide resistance gene cluster VanA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000234','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000028,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000029','This inducible cluster confers high resistance to both vancomycin and teicoplanin by allowing restructuring of peptidoglycan precursors to end in D-Ala-D-Lac. The vanA gene cluster can be located either on plasmids or on the chromosome.\n\nGene orientation: vanRSHAXYZ'),(278,'ARO:3000237','TolC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000344,part_of ARO:3000373,part_of ARO:3000384,part_of ARO:3000503,part_of ARO:3000545,part_of ARO:3000787,part_of ARO:3000788,part_of ARO:3004083,part_of ARO:3004598','TolC is a protein subunit of many multidrug efflux complexes in Gram negative bacteria. It is an outer membrane efflux protein and is constitutively open. Regulation of efflux activity is often at its periplasmic entrance by other components of the efflux complex.'),(279,'ARO:3000238','glycopeptide resistance gene cluster VanB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000234','','This inducible cluster confers resistance to vancomycin but orga