 conversion of p-aminobenzoic acid to dihydropteroic acid as part of the tetrahydrofolic acid biosynthetic pathway. Tetrahydrofolic acid is essential for folate synthesis, a precursor of many nucleotides and amino acids. Many sulfamides are taken with trimethoprim, an inhibitor of dihydrofolate reductase, also disturbing the trihydrofolic acid synthesis pathway.'),(313,'ARO:3000284','tetroxoprim','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000171','','Tetroxoprim is a trimethoprim derivative that inhibits bacterial dihydrofolate reductase.'),(314,'ARO:3000299','phosphonopyruvate decarboxylase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000082','','Stabilizes the C-P bond in phosphonopyruvate formed by phophoenolpyruvate mutase by catalyzing the self-removal of the carboxyl group.'),(315,'ARO:3000300','lsaA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004472','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000066,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000584,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000674,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3001317','LsaA is an ABC-F subfamily protein expressed in Enterococcus faecalis. It confers resistance to clindamycin, quinupristin-dalfopristin, and dalfopristin.'),(316,'ARO:3000309','emrD','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','','EmrD is a multidrug transporter from the Major Facilitator Superfamily (MFS) primarily found in Escherichia coli. EmrD couples efflux of amphipathic compounds with proton import across the plasma membrane.'),(317,'ARO:3000315','determinant of macrolide resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000000','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000000','Enzymes, other proteins or other gene products shown clinically to confer resistance to macrolide antibiotics.'),(318,'ARO:3000316','mphA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000333','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000027,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000057,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000065,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000158,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000176,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000