iting peptide synthesis by interacting with the 23S RNA of the 50S ribosomal subunit.'),(358,'ARO:3000383','determinant of rifamycin resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000000','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000157','Enzymes, other proteins, or other gene products shown clinically to confer resistance to rifamycin (rifampin) antibiotics.'),(359,'ARO:3000384','AcrAB-TolC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000030,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000169,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000385,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000637,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000704,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000870','AcrAB-TolC is a tripartite RND efflux system that confers resistance to tetracycline, chloramphenicol, ampicillin, nalidixic acid, and rifampin  in Gram-negative bacteria. The system spans the cell membrane (AcrB) and the outer-membrane (TolC), and is linked together in the periplasm by AcrA.'),(360,'ARO:3000385','chloramphenicol','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000387','','Chloramphenicol is a bacteriostatic antimicrobial originally derived from the bacterium Streptomyces venezuelae. It was the first antibiotic to be manufactured synthetically on a large scale. It functions by inhibiting peptidyl transferase activity of the bacterial ribosome, binding to A2451 and A2452 residues in the 23S rRNA of the 50S ribosomal subunit and preventing peptide bond formation.'),(361,'ARO:3000386','MexAB-OprM','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000000,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000032,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000044,confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008,confers_resistance_to ARO:3000282,confers_resistance_to ARO:3003706,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000036,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000060,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:000006