protects the ribosome from inactivation due to antibiotic binding.'),(436,'ARO:3000524','cpxAR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000491,regulates ARO:3000787,regulates ARO:3004082','CpxAR is a two-component regulatory system that involves a sensor kinase, CpxA, and the regulator CpxR. When the membrane envelope is stressed, CpxAR promotes acrD and mdtABC expression to confer multidrug resistance through efflux.'),(437,'ARO:3000525','antibiotic A40926','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000081','','A40926 is a glycopeptide antibiotic produced by Nonomuraea sp. ATCC 39727. It is precusor of the second-generation glycopeptide antibiotic dalbavancin.'),(438,'ARO:3000526','cmeR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000773','CmeR is a repressor for the CmeABC multidrug efflux pump, binding to the cmeABC promoter region.'),(439,'ARO:3000527','polyamine antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000003','','Polyamine antibiotics are organic compounds having two or more primary amino groups.'),(440,'ARO:3000528','chlortetracycline','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000050','','Chlortetracycline was an early, first-generation tetracycline antibiotic developed in the 1940`s. It inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by binding to the 30S subunit of bacterial ribosomes, preventing the aminoacyl-tRNA from binding to the ribosome.'),(441,'ARO:3000529','determinant of mupirocin resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000000','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000554','Enzymes, other proteins or other gene products shown clinically to confer resistance to mupirocin antibiotics. Mutations in ileS is shown to confer low-level mupirocin resistance, while high-level resistance is conferred by the presence of alternative isoleucyl-tRNA synthetases.'),(442,'ARO:3000530','rifabutin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000157','','Rifabutin is a semisynthetic rifamycin used in tuberculosis therapy. It inhibits DNA-dependent RNA synthesis.'),(443,'ARO:3000531','baeSR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000491,regulates ARO:3000787,regulates ARO:3004082','BaeSR is a two component regulatory system for efflux proteins in Gram-negative bacteria. BaeR is a response regulator, while BaeS is a sensor kinase.'),(444,'ARO:3000532','aminocoumarin biosynthesis','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000082','','Biosynthesis of aminocoumarin antibiotics.'),(445,'ARO:3000533','macA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000545','MacA is a membrane fusion protein that forms an antibiotic efflux complex with MacB and TolC. macA corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.'),(446,'ARO:3000534','rifapentine','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000157','','Rifapentine is a semisynthetic rifamycin that inhibits DNA-dependent RNA synthesis. It is often used in the treatment of tuberculosis and leprosy.'),(447,'ARO:3000535','macB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000545','MacB is an ATP-binding cassette (ABC) transporter that exports macrolides with 14- or 15- membered lactones. It forms an antibiotic efflux complex with MacA and TolC. macB corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 and 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.'),(448,'ARO:3000536','Streptomyces spheroides novobiocin biosynthetic gene cluster','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000532','','Novobiocin is produced from biosynthetic clusters in Streptomyces spheroides and Streptomyces niveus.'),(449,'ARO:3000545','MacAB-TolC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010001','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006','MacAB-TolC is an ABC efflux pump complex expressed in E. coli and Salmonella enterica. It confers resistance to macrolides, including erythromycin.'),(450,'ARO:3000546','Streptomyces roseochromogenus subsp. oscitans clorobiocin biosynthetic gene cluster','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000532','','Clorobiocin is produced by a biosynthetic cluster in Streptomyces roseochromogenus subsp. oscitans'),(451,'ARO:3000547','arlRS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000391','ArlRS is a two-component regulatory system for NorA. ArlS phosphorylates ArlR to promote NorA expression.'),(452,'ARO:3000548','Streptomyces rishiriensis strain DSM 40489 coumermycin A1 biosynthetic gene cluster','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000532','','Coumermycin A1 is produced by a biosynthetic cluster in Streptomyces rishiriensis.'),(453,'ARO:3000549','adeS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000770','AdeS is a sensor kinase in the AdeRS regulatory system of AdeABC. It is essential for AdeABC expression.'),(454,'ARO:3000550','aztreonam','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000004','','Aztreonam was the first monobactam discovered, and is greatly effective against Gram-negative bacteria while inactive against Gram-positive bacteria. Artreonam is a poor substrate for beta-lactamases, and may even act as an inhibitor. In Gram-negative bacteria, Aztreonam interferes with filamentation, inhibiting cell division and leading to cell death.'),(455,'ARO:3000551','organoarsenic antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000003','','Organoarsenic antibiotics are arsenic-containing compounds with antibacterial effects. The organoarsenic antibiotic arsphenamine and its derivatives were developed in the 1910s as the first modern chemotherapeutic agents.'),(456,'ARO:3000552','arsphenamine','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000551','','Arsphenamine, also known as Salvarsan and 606, is a drug that was used beginning in the 1910s to treat syphilis and trypanosomiasis. It is an organoarsenic compound and was the first modern chemotherapeutic agent.'),(457,'ARO:3000553','adeR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000770','AdeR is a positive regulator of AdeABC efflux system. AdeR inactivation leads to susceptibility to aminoglycoside antibiotics.'),(458,'ARO:3000554','mupirocin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000003','','Mupirocin, also known as pseudomonic acid, is a bacteriostatic polyketide antibiotic from Pseudomonas fluorescens used to treat S. aureus and MRSA. It inhibits Ile tRNA synthetase.'),(459,'ARO:3000555','macrolide biosynthesis','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000082','','Biosynthesis of macrolide antibiotics.'),(460,'ARO:3000556','tet(44)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000069,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000152,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000528,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000667,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000668','Tet44 is a tetracycline resistance gene found in Campylobacter fetus, and binds to the ribosome to confer antibiotic resistance as a ribosomal protection protein.'),(461,'ARO:3000557','antibiotic inactivation enzyme','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000000','','Enzyme that catalyzes the inactivation of an antibiotic resulting in resistance.  Inactivation includes chemical modification, destruction, etc.'),(462,'ARO:3000558','sulfonamide resistant dihydropteroate synthase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000408','','Folate is an essential precursor for many nucleotides and amino acids, making folate biosynthesis a desirable target for antibiotics. Mutation to enzymes within the folate biosynthetic pathway can reverse antibiotic action. Modification of dihydropteroate synthase (folP) can result in resistance to sulfonamide antibiotics. Resistance can be conferred by mutation to the native folP gene or by acquiring a resistant DHPS (sul) gene through gene transfer. The sul gene has three known variants (sul1, sul2, sul3) and encodes a highly resistant dihydropteroate synthase that can be acquired via transposons or plasmids.'),(463,'ARO:3000559','adeN','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000772','AdeN is a repressor of AdeIJK, a RND-type efflux pump in Acinetobacter baumannii. Its inactivation increases expression of AdeJ.'),(464,'ARO:3000560','Erm 23S ribosomal RNA methyltransferase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000240,ARO:3000241,ARO:3000315,ARO:3004274','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000000,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000017,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000026','Erm proteins are part of the RNA methyltransferase family and methylate A2058 (E. coli nomenclature) of the 23S ribosomal RNA conferring degrees of resistance to Macrolides, Lincosamides and Streptogramin b. This is called the MLSb phenotype.'),(465,'ARO:3000561','tet(30)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051','Tet30 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in agrobacterium, a Gram-negative bacterium.'),(466,'ARO:3000565','tet(38)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051','Tet38 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in the Gram-positive Staphylococcus aureus. It is regulated by mgrA, which also regulates NorB.'),(467,'ARO:3000566','tet(39)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051','Tet39 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Gram-negative bacteria, including Brevundimonas, Stenotrophomonas, Enterobacter, Alcaligenes, Acinetobacter, and Providencia.'),(468,'ARO:3000567','tet(40)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051','Tet40 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in the Gram-positive Clostridium. It is similar to tetA(P).'),(469,'ARO:3000568','subclass B1 (metallo-) beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000004','','Subclass B1 possess a binuclear active site.  Within this active site can be either one or two Zn(II) ions.  This subclass is able to hydrolyze penicillins, cephalosporins and carbapenems.  This is the most clinically relevant subclass of MBLs.'),(470,'ARO:3000569','tet(41)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051','Tet41 is a tetracycline efflux pump found in Serratia, a Gram-negative bacterium.  It is related to Acinetobacter Tet(39).'),(471,'ARO:3000570','subclass B2 (metallo-) beta-lactamase','antibiotic