-lactams.'),(510,'ARO:3000619','fluoroquinolone resistant parC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000274,ARO:3000452','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,derives_from ARO:3000735','ParC is a subunit of topoisomerase IV, which decatenates and relaxes DNA to allow access to genes for transcription or translation. Point mutations in ParC prevent fluoroquinolone antibiotics from inhibiting DNA synthesis, and confer low-level resistance. Higher-level resistance results from both gyrA and parC mutations.'),(511,'ARO:3000620','adeL','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000771','AdeL is a regulator of AdeFGH in Acinetobacter baumannii. AdeL mutations are associated with AdeFGH overexpression and multidrug resistance.'),(512,'ARO:3000621','PC1 beta-lactamase (blaZ)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004197','part_of ARO:3000262','The blaZ beta-lactamase is found in Bacillus subtilis and Staphylococcus aureus.'),(513,'ARO:3000622','colistin A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000022,ARO:0000067','','Colistin A, or polymyxin E1, has a 6-octanoic acid lipid tail. Polymyxins disrupt the cell membrane of Gram-negative bacteria.'),(514,'ARO:3000624','colistin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000022,ARO:0000067','','Colistin B, or polymyxin E2, has a 6-heptanoic acid lipid tail. Polymyxins disrupt the cell membrane of Gram-negative bacteria.'),(515,'ARO:3000625','polymyxin B1','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000022,ARO:3000454','','Polymyxin B1 is in the family of polymyxin lipopeptides with a 6-methyloctanoic acid acyl group. These antibiotics disrupt the cell membrane of Gram-negative bacteria.'),(516,'ARO:3000626','polymyxin B2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000022,ARO:3000454','','Polymyxin B2 is in the family of polymyxin lipopeptides with a 6-methylheptanoic acid acyl group. These antibiotics disrupt the cell membrane of Gram-negative bacteria.'),(517,'ARO:3000627','polymyxin B3','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000022,ARO:3000454','','Polymyxin B3 is in the family of polymyxin lipopeptides with an octanoic acid acyl group. These antibiotics disrupt the cell membrane of Gram-negative bacteria.'),(518,'ARO:3000628','polymyxin B4','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000022,ARO:3000454','','Polymyxin B4 is in the family of polymyxin lipopeptides with a heptanoic acid acyl group. These antibiotics disrupt the cell membrane of Gram-negative bacteria.'),(519,'ARO:3000629','bacitracin A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000041','','Bacitracin A is the primary component of bacitracin. It contains many uncommon amino acids and interferes with bacterial cell wall synthesis.'),(520,'ARO:3000630','bacitracin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000041','','Bacitracin B is a component of bacitracin, an antibiotic mixture that interferes with bacterial cell wall synthesis. It differs from Bacitracin A with a valine instead of an isoleucine in its peptide.'),(521,'ARO:3000631','bacitracin F','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000041','','Bacitracin F is a component of bacitracin, an antibiotic mixture that interferes with bacterial cell wall synthesis. It is formed when the thiazoline ring of bacitracin A is oxidatively deaminated.'),(522,'ARO:3000632','benzylpenicillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Benzylpenicillin, commonly referred to as penicillin G, is effective against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria. It is unstable in acid.'),(523,'ARO:3000633','phenoxymethylpenicillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Phenoxymethylpenicillin, or penicillin V, is a penicillin derivative that is acid stable but less active than benzylpenicillin (penicillin G).'),(524,'ARO:3000634','propicillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Propicillin is an orally taken penicillin derivative that has high absorption but poor activity.'),(525,'ARO:3000635','dicloxacillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Dicloxacillin is a penicillin derivative that has an extra chlorine atom in comparison to cloxacillin. While more active than cloxacillin, its high affinity for serum protein reduces its activity in human serum in vitro.'),(526,'ARO:3000636','flucloxacillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Flucloxacillin is similar to cloxacillin, with an extra additional fluorine atom.'),(527,'ARO:3000637','ampicillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Ampicillin is a penicillin derivative that is highly acid stable, with its activity similar to benzylpenicillin.'),(528,'ARO:3000638','azlocillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Azlocillin is a semisynthetic derivative of penicillin that is notably active against Ps. aeruginosa and other Gram-negative bacteria.'),(529,'ARO:3000639','mezlocillin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Mezlocillin is a penicillin derivative taken parenterally.'),(530,'ARO:3000640','doripenem','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000020','','Doripenem is a carbapenem with a broad range of activity against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, and along with meropenem, it is the most active beta-lactam antibiotic against Pseudomonas aeruginosa. It inhibits bacterial cell wall synthesis.'),(531,'ARO:3000641','cefalexin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefalexin is a cephalosporin antibiotic that causes filamentation. It is resistant to staphylococcal beta-lactamase, but degraded by enterobacterial beta-lactamases.'),(532,'ARO:3000642','cefadroxil','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefadroxil, or p-hydroxycephalexin, is an cephalosporin antibiotic similar to cefalexin.'),(533,'ARO:3000643','cefotiam','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefotiam is a cephalosporin antibiotic with similar activity to cefuroxime but more active against enterobacteria. It is consumed orally as the prodrug cefotiam hexetil.'),(534,'ARO:3000644','cefaclor','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefaclor is a semisynthetic cephalosporin derived from cephalexin. It has broad-spectrum antibiotic activity.'),(535,'ARO:3000645','cefotaxime','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefotaxime is a semisynthetic cephalosporin taken parenterally. It is resistant to most beta-lactamases and active against Gram-negative rods and cocci due to its aminothiazoyl and methoximino functional groups.'),(536,'ARO:3000646','cefixime','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefixime is a cephalosporin resistant to most beta-lactamases. It is active against many enterobacteria, but activity against staphylococci is poor.'),(537,'ARO:3000647','cefpodoxime','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefpodoxime is a semisynthetic cephalosporin that acts similarly to cefotaxime with broad-spectrum activity. It is stable to many plasmid-mediated beta-lactamses. Cefpodoxime is consumed as the prodrug cefpodoxime proxetil.'),(538,'ARO:3000648','ceftibuten','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Ceftibuten is a semisynthetic cephalosporin active against Gram-negative bacilli. It is resistant against many plasmid-mediated beta-lactamases.'),(539,'ARO:3000649','cefditoren','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefditoren is a semisynthetic cephalosporin active against staphylococci, streptococci, and and most enterobacteria. It is resistant to staphylococcal and most enterobacterial beta-lactamases, and is usually taken as the prodrug cefditoren pivoxil.'),(540,'ARO:3000650','cefdinir','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefdinir is similar to cefixime with a modified side-chain at its 7-amino position. It also shares similar activity with cefixime but is more active against staphylococci. It has also be shown to enhance phagocytosis.'),(541,'ARO:3000651','ceftaroline','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Ceftaroline is a novel cephalosporin active against methicillin resistant Staphylococcus aureus. Like other cephalosporins it binds penicillin-binding proteins to inhibit cell wall synthesis. It strongly binds with PBP2a, associated with methicillin resistance. It is taken orally as the prodrug ceftaroline fosamil.'),(542,'ARO:3000652','isepamicin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','A semi-synthetic derivative of gentamicin B (hydroxyamino propionyl genamicin B). It is modified to combat microbial inactivation and has a slightly larger spectrum of activity compared to other aminoglycosides, including Ser marcescens, Enterobacteria, and K pneumoniae.'),(543,'ARO:3000653','G418','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','A gentamicin class aminoglycoside antibiotic often used in mammalian cell culture work as a selectable marker for the neo cassette (APH3`).'),(544,'ARO:3000654','arbekacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','A synthetic derivative (1-N-(4-amino-2-hydroxybutyryl) of dibekacin used in Japan. It is active against methicillin-resistant Staph. aureus and shows synergy with ampicillin when treating gentamicin and vancomycin resistant enterocci.'),(545,'ARO:3000655','gentamicin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','Gentamicin B is a semisynthetic aminoglycoside antibacterial.'),(546,'ARO:3000656','AcrS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','part_of ARO:3004083,regulates ARO:3000384,regulates ARO:3000503','AcrS is a repressor of the AcrAB efflux complex and is associated with the expression of AcrEF. AcrS is believed to regulate a switch between AcrAB and AcrEF efflux.'),(547,'ARO:3000657','paromomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','An aminoglycoside antibiotic used for the treatment of parasitic infections. It is similar to neomycin sharing a similar spectrum of activity, but its hydroxyl group at the 6`-position instead of an amino group makes it resistant to AAC(6`) modifying enzymes.'),(548,'ARO:3000658','lividomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','Lividomycins are aminoglycosidic antibiotics produced by Streptomyces lividus. They contain 2-amino-2,3-dideoxy-D-glucose.'),(549,'ARO:3000659','gatifloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Gatifloxacin is an 8-methoxy, 7-piperazinyl, 6-fluoroquinolone that can be taken orally or by intravenous administration. It is active against most Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, but inactive against non-fermenting Gram-negative rods including Pseudomonas aeruginosa.'),(550,'ARO:3000660','lomefloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Lomefloxacin is a difluoropiperazinyl quinolone, sharing similar activities with other fluoroquinolones. It is used to treat urinary tract infections. Relative to other fluoroquinolones, it has a longer half life and has higher serum concentrations.'),(551,'ARO:3000661','nalidixic acid','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Nalidixic acid is a quinolone derivative of naphthyridine active against many enterobacteria, but ineffective against Ps aeruginosa, Gram-positive bacteria, and anaerobes. Acquired resistance is common in nalidixic acid treatments.'),(552,'ARO:3000662','norfloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Norfloxacin is a 6-fluoro, 7-piperazinyl quinolone with a wide range of activity against Gram-negative bacteria. It is inactive against most anaerobes.'),(553,'ARO:3000663','ofloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Ofloxacin is a 6-fluoro, 7-piperazinyl quinolone with a methyl-substituted oxazine ring. It has a broad spectrum of activity including many enterobacteria and mycoplasma but most anaerobes are resistant.'),(554,'ARO:3000664','trovafloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Trovafloxacin is a trifluoroquinalone with a broad spectrum of activity that acts by inhibiting the uncoiling of supercoiled DNA. While potent against many Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, it is less active against pseudomonads and Cl. difficile. It is usually taken as the prodrug trovafloxacin mesylate or alatrofloxacin mesylate for oral or intravenous administration, respectively.'),(555,'ARO:3000665','grepafloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Grepafloxacin is a broad-spectrum antibacterial quinoline. It is no longer taken due to its high toxicity.'),(556,'ARO:3000666','sparfloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Sparfloxacin is a dimethylpiperazinyl difluoroquinolone that acts by inhibiting DNA gyrase. It is active against aerobic Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, as well as some mycobacteria. It has moderate activity against some anaerobes.'),(557,'ARO:3000667','demeclocycline','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000050','','Demeclocycline is a tetracycline analog with 7-chloro and 6-methyl groups. Due to its fast absorption and slow excretion, it maintains higher effective blood levels compared to other tetracyclines.'),(558,'ARO:3000668','oxytetracycline','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000050','','Oxytetracycline is a derivative of tetracycline with a 5-hydroxyl group. Its activity is similar to other tetracyclines.'),(559,'ARO:3000669','pristinamycin IIA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000034','','Pristinamycin IIA is a streptogramin A antibiotic.'),(560,'ARO:3000670','pleuromutilin antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000003','','Pleuromutilins are natural fungal products that target bacterial protein translation by binding the the 23S rRNA, blocking the ribosome P site at the 50S subunit. They are mostly used for agriculture and veterinary purposes.'),(561,'ARO:3000671','tiamulin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000670','','Tiamulin is a pleuromutilin derivative currently used in veterinary medicine. It binds to the 23 rRNA of the 50S ribosomal subunit to inhibit protein translation.'),(562,'ARO:3000672','madumycin II','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000034','','Madumycin II is a streptogramin A antibiotic.'),(563,'ARO:3000673','griseoviridin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000034','','Griseoviridin is a streptogramin A antibiotic.'),(564,'ARO:3000674','dalfopristin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000034','','Dalfopristin is a water-soluble semi-synthetic derivative of pristinamycin IIA. It is produced by Streptomyces pristinaespiralis and is used in combination with quinupristin in a 7:3 ratio. Both work together to inhibit protein synthesis, and is active against Gram-positive bacteria.'),(565,'ARO:3000675','pristinamycin IB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000050','','Pristinamycin IB is a class B streptogramin similar to pristinamycin IA, the former containing a N-methyl-4-(methylamino)phenylalanine instead of a N-methyl-4-(dimethylamino)phenylalanine in its class A streptogramin counterpart (one less methyl group).'),(566,'ARO:3000676','H-NS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000373,regulates ARO:3000503,regulates ARO:3000788,regulates ARO:3004083','H-NS is a histone-like protein involved in global gene regulation in Gram-negative bacteria. It is a repressor of the membrane fusion protein genes acrE, mdtE, and emrK as well as nearby genes of many RND-type multidrug exporters.'),(567,'ARO:3000677','virginiamycin S2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000050','','Virginiamycin S2 is a streptogramin B antibiotic.'),(568,'ARO:3000678','vernamycin B-gamma','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000050','','Vernamycin B-gamma is a class B streptogramin derived from virginiamycin S1.'),(569,'ARO:3000679','vernamycin C','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000050','','Vernamycin C is a streptogramin B antibiotic.'),(570,'ARO:3000680','patricin A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000050','','Patricin A is a streptogramin B antibiotic.'),(571,'ARO:3000681','patricin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000050','','Patricin B is a streptogramin B antibiotic.'),(572,'ARO:3000682','ostreogrycin B3','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000050','','Ostreogrycin B3 is a derivative of pristinamycin IA, with an additional 3-hydroxy group on its 4-oxopipecolic acid.'),(573,'ARO:3000683','sulfacetamide','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000282','','Sulfacetamide is a very soluable sulfonamide antibiotic previously used to treat urinary tract infections. Its relatively low activity and toxicity to those with Stevens-Johnson syndrome have reduced its use and availability.'),(574,'ARO:3000684','mafenide','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000282','','Mafenide is a sulfonamide used topically for treating burns.'),(575,'ARO:3000685','arylomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000035','','Arylomycins are lipopeptide antibiotics, sharing a lipohexapeptide with a C-terminal tripeptide macrolide and varying by the length of its alkyl chains.'),(576,'ARO:3000686','thiostrepton','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000053','','Thiostrepton is a cyclic peptide active against Gram-positive bacteria. It is produced by streptomyces bacteria.'),(577,'ARO:3000687','moenomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000035','','Moemomycin antibiotics are phosphoglycolipids that contain a 3-phosphoglyceric acid, often used as a mixture. They inhibit petidoglycan glycosyltransferases to prevent bacterial cell wall biosynthesis.'),(578,'ARO:3000688','furazolidone','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004116','','Furazolidone is a nitrofuran antibiotic that is a non-ionic synthetic compound. It is taken orally and is active against many enteric pathogens. Furazolidone also has antiprotozoal activity and acts by inhibiting monoamine oxidase.'),(579,'ARO:3000689','metronidazole','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004115','','Metronidazole is a nitroimidazole that is active against anaerobic bacteria and protozoa. It is not effective against aerobic bacteria. Nitroimidazoles act by oxidizing DNA causing strand breaks and cell death.'),(580,'ARO:3000690','bleomycinic acid','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000053,ARO:3000081','','Bleomycinic acid is a glycopeptide antibiotic produced by Streptomyces verticillus taken as a mixture of bleomycins. It induces stand breaks in bacterial nucleic acids.'),(581,'ARO:3000691','bleomycin A2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000053,ARO:3000081','','Bleomycin A2 is a glycopeptide antibiotic produced by Streptomyces verticillus taken as a mixture of bleomycins. It induces stand breaks in bacterial nucleic acids.'),(582,'ARO:3000692','bleomycin B2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000053,ARO:3000081','','Bleomycin B2 is a glycopeptide antibiotic produced by Streptomyces verticillus taken as a mixture of bleomycins. It induces stand breaks in bacterial nucleic acids.'),(583,'ARO:3000693','defensin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000053','','Defensins are natural cationic peptides that have antibiotic properties. It is part of the innate immune system of plants and animals.'),(584,'ARO:3000694','magainin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000053','','Magainins are antimicrobial peptides produced by amphibians skil cells as part of their innate immune system. It is active against a broad range of gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria, fungi and protozoa.'),(585,'ARO:3000695','actinomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000053','','Actinomycins are peptide antibiotics that interact with DNA. This prevents RNA synthesis, thus preventing the production of proteins vital to the cell.'),(586,'ARO:3000696','Dactinomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000695','','Dactinomycin, also known as Actinomycin D, is a cyclic peptide antibiotic that interacts with DNA to inhibit RNA synthesis.'),(587,'ARO:3000697','moenomycin A1','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000035,ARO:3000687','','Moenomycin A1 is a major component of moenomycin mixtures. It is produced by Streptomyces ghanaensis, S. bambergiensis, S. ederensis, and S. geysiriensis.'),(588,'ARO:3000698','sulfasalazine','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000282','','Sulfasalazine is a derivative of the early sulfonamide sulfapyridine (salicylazosulfapyridine). It was developed to increase water solubility and is taken orally for ulcerative colitis.'),(589,'ARO:3000699','sulfamethizole','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000282','','Sulfamethizole is a short-acting sulfonamide that inhibits dihydropteroate synthetase.'),(590,'ARO:3000700','lividomycin A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016,ARO:3000658','','Lividomycin A is a pentasaccharide antibiotic which interferes with bacterial protein synthesis.'),(591,'ARO:3000701','lividomycin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016,ARO:3000658','','Lividomycin B is a derivative of lividomycin A with a removed mannose group (demannosyllividomycin A). Livodomycins interfere with bacterial protein synthesis.'),(592,'ARO:3000702','acrR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000219,ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000384','AcrR is a repressor of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrR mutations result in high level antibiotic resistance.'),(593,'ARO:3000704','cefalotin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cefalotin is a semisynthetic cephalosporin antibiotic activate against staphylococci. It is resistant to staphylococci beta-lactamases but hydrolyzed by enterobacterial beta-lactamases.'),(594,'ARO:3000705','isopenicillin N','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Isopenicillin N is a natural penicillin derivative produced by Penicillium chrysogenum with activity similar to penicillin N.'),(595,'ARO:3000706','penicillin N','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Penicillin N is a penicillin derivative produced by Cephalosporium acremonium.'),(596,'ARO:3000707','antibiotic mixture','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000003','','Mixtures of antibiotics are commonly used clinically. These mixtures link to antibiotic molecules that are also listed in their respective families under antibiotic molecules. i.e. `Gramicidin A` is part of the mixture `gramicidin D`, while `Gramicidin A` is also a `gramicidin`, which is a `peptide antibiotic`.'),(597,'ARO:3000708','antibiotic target','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000001','','Antibiotic targets are components of the bacterial cell usually unique to bacteria or significantly different from their eukaryotic counterparts to allow for selective antibacterial activity. Exceptions include antibiotics that are converted to an active form inside the bacterium. Resistance mechanisms may modify these targets to protect bacteria from the effects of antibiotics.'),(598,'ARO:3000709','cell wall synthesis enzyme targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','','Cell wall biosynthesis provides bacteria with a layer of peptidoglycan that provides rigidity and protects the cell from lysis due to osmotic pressure. Cell wall structures vary significantly between Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, while mycobacteria have a unique cell wall composition.'),(599,'ARO:3000710','cell membrane component targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','targeted_by ARO:0000022,targeted_by ARO:3000123,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000200,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000222,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000223,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000224,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000622,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000624,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000625,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000626,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000627,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000628,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000693,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000694','Interaction with the cell membrane phospholipids interferes with membrane permeability and integrity, leading to the leakage of cell contents. The outer membrane of Gram-negative bacteria is particularly sensitive.'),(600,'ARO:3000711','protein synthesis machinery targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','','Protein synthesis in bacteria is accomplished by cytosolic ribosomes that are structurally different from eukaryotic ribosomes, and thus a target for many antibiotics. By inhibiting ribosomal activity, either by directly binding to the ribosome or interacting with co-factors, antibiotics prevent protein synthesis.'),(601,'ARO:3000712','nucleic acid synthesis machinery targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','','Bacterial DNA and RNA synthesis includes many enzymes unique to bacteria that are targeted by antibiotics.'),(602,'ARO:3000713','nucleic acid targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','','Nucleic acids can also be targeted by antibiotics. These drugs are usually converted to an active form by enzymes unique to bacteria to prevent toxicity to the host.'),(603,'ARO:3000714','folate synthesis enzyme targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','','Enzymes in the folate synthesis pathway are targeted by two main classes of antibiotics: sulfonamides and diaminopyrimidines. Inhibition of these enzymes block the production of key precursors for nucleotides and amino acids.'),(604,'ARO:3000715','isoprenoid synthesis enzyme targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','','Enzymes in this pathway generate important precursors for macromolecules. While eukaryotes and prokaryotes both synthesize isoprenoids, many bacteria and notably mycobacteria use an alternative pathway that is targeted by antibiotics.'),(605,'ARO:3000716','mycolic acid synthesis enzyme targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000520','Mycolic acids are produced by mycobacteria. These fatty acids are required for the construction of cell walls. Enzymes that are targeted by antibiotics include synthases, elongases, and dehydrogenases.'),(606,'ARO:3000717','antibiotic sensitive signal peptidase I','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000685','Signal peptidase I is a bacterial signal peptidase that cleaves signal peptides from translated proteins. These signal peptides direct proteins to their destination, and then must be cleaved in order to function.'),(607,'ARO:3000718','marR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000219,ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000384','MarR is a repressor of the mar operon marRAB, thus regulating the expression of marA, the activator of multidrug efflux pump AcrAB.'),(608,'ARO:3000719','bacitracin sensitive isoprenyl pyrophosphate','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000709','targeted_by ARO:0000041,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000629,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000630,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000631','Isoprepnyl pyrophosphate removes a phosphate group that is added from the peptidoglycan subunit to permit its transfer across the cell membrane. The phosphate group must be removed before its incorporation into peptidoglycan macromolecules.'),(609,'ARO:3000720','acyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000721','targeted_by_drug ARO:0000028,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000029,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000022,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000117,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000120,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000184,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000189,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000466,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000488,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000525,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000767','The acyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine group is found at the terminal end of the pentapeptide chains of peptidoglycan subunits. Antibiotics that bind to this group block the addition of subunits, inhibiting peptidoglycan synthesis. This group is most accessible in Gram-postive bacteria.'),(610,'ARO:3000721','cell wall component targeted by antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000708','','The cell wall is unique to bacteria and provides rigidity and protects the cell from lysis due to osmotic pressure. Its characteristic component is peptidoglycan, though cell wall structures vary significantly between Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, as well as mycobacteria.'),(611,'ARO:3000722','cycloserine sensitive alanine racemase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000709','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000760','Alanine racemase converts the natural L-alanine to the D-alanine required in the pentapeptide chains in peptidoglycan. It is found in both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.'),(612,'ARO:3000723','cycloserine sensitive D-alanine synthetase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000709','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000760','D-Alanine synthetase joins two D-alanines before their addition to the pentapeptide chains of peptidoglycan. It is found in both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.'),(613,'ARO:3000724','fosfomycin sensitive pyruvyl transferase (murA)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000709','targeted_by_drug ARO:0000025','Pyruvyl transferase is responsible for the conversion of N-acetylglucosamine (NAG) to N-acetylmuramic acid (NAMA). NAMA is a part of the macromolecular backbone of peptidoglycans. Pyruvyl transferase is found in both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.'),(614,'ARO:3000725','antibiotic sensitive arabinosyltransferase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000709','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000497','Arabinosyl transferases allow for the polymerization of arabinose to form arabinan. Arabanan is required for formation of mycobacterial cell walls.'),(615,'ARO:3000726','pentaglycyl bridge','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000721','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000189','The pentaglycyl bridge is part of Gram-positive peptidoglycan, allowing the formation of a thick and rigid cell wall.'),(616,'ARO:3000727','50S ribosomal subunit','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000711','targeted_by ARO:0000000','The larger of two ribosomal subunits that make up the 70S bacterial ribosome.'),(617,'ARO:3000728','30S ribosomal subunit','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000711','targeted_by ARO:0000042','The smaller of two ribosomal subunits that make up the 70S bacterial ribosome.'),(618,'ARO:3000729','ribosomal complex','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000711','targeted_by ARO:3000490,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000018','The ribosomal complex can be targeted by antibiotics that stabilize the entire complex and prevent further translation. These antibiotics target both subunits in the process of protein translation.'),(619,'ARO:3000730','elongation factor G','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000711','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000759','Elongation factor G (EF-G) provides energy for the translocation step in protein synthesis. Antibiotics that target EF-G allow one round of translocation but prevent EF-G from dissociating from the ribosome-RNA complex.'),(620,'ARO:3000731','elongation factor Tu','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000711','targeted_by ARO:3001219,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000586,targeted_by_drug ARO:3001237,targeted_by_drug ARO:3001242,targeted_by_drug ARO:3001310,targeted_by_drug ARO:3003414','Elongation factor Tu is required for peptide elongation in bacterial protein synthesis.'),(621,'ARO:3000732','antibiotic sensitive Isoleucyl-tRNA transferase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000711','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000554','Isoleucyl-tRNA transferase recognizes isoleucine codons and works with the ribosome to incorporate isoleucine amino acids into polypeptide chains. It can be targeted by antibiotics that have an analog of isoleucine through competitive inhibition.'),(622,'ARO:3000733','fluoroquinolone sensitive gyrA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003254','targeted_by ARO:0000001,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000023,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000036,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000071,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000074,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000659,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000660,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000661,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000662,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000663,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000664,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000665,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000666,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000762,targeted_by_drug ARO:3004010,targeted_by_drug ARO:3004011,targeted_by_drug ARO:3004012,targeted_by_drug ARO:3004013','DNA gyrase is responsible for DNA supercoiling and consists of two alpha and two beta subunits. Binding the alpha-subunit is sufficient to inhibit DNA supercoiling.'),(623,'ARO:3000734','antibiotic sensitive DNA topoisomerase subunit gyrB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000766','targeted_by ARO:3000103,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000111,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000132,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000150','DNA gyrase is responsible for DNA supercoiling and consists of two alpha and two beta subunits. Binding the beta-subunit is sufficient to inhibit DNA supercoiling.'),(624,'ARO:3000735','fluoroquinolone sensitive parC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003256','targeted_by ARO:0000001,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000036,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000071,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000662,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000663,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000762','subunit of the DNA topoisomerase IV sensitive to fluoroquinolone'),(625,'ARO:3000736','rho transcription terminator factor','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000712','targeted_by_drug ARO:0000055','The rho transcription terminator factor moves along RNA as it is transcribed, unwinding the RNA from the DNA. It is also responsible for recognizing transcription termination pause sites, slowing down RNA polymerase and allowing mRNA to be released.'),(626,'ARO:3000737','rifamycin sensitive beta-subunit of RNA polymerase (rpoB)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003277','targeted_by ARO:3000157,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000169,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000517,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000530,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000534','The beta-subunit of RNA polymerase is targeted as a complex. When blocked, RNA strand elongation cannot continue after the first few nucleotides.'),(627,'ARO:3000738','deoxyribonucleic acid','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000713','targeted_by ARO:0000053,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000075,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000690,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000691,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000692','Antibiotics can target DNA to cause strand breaks or prevent transcription. The activity of these antibiotics can be context dependent: some antibiotics are converted to an active form only in certain species, while others target DNA as it is being transcribed.'),(628,'ARO:3000739','RNA guanosine binding site','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000740','targeted_by ARO:3000490,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000018','RNA intron self-splicing action can be inhibited by antibiotics that target a G-binding site to compete with the guanosine cofactor.'),(629,'ARO:3000740','ribonucleic acid','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000713','targeted_by ARO:0000053,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000690,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000691,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000692','Many types of ribonucleic acids (RNAs) are targeted by antibiotics, including mRNA templates and ribosomal RNA. Some antibiotics target all RNAs and cause strand breaks.'),(630,'ARO:3000741','transcription complex DNA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000738','targeted_by ARO:3000695,targeted_by_dr