','antibiotic sensitive peptidyl transferase (23S rRNA)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000740','part_of ARO:3000727,targeted_by ARO:0000017,targeted_by ARO:0000026,targeted_by ARO:0000034,targeted_by ARO:3000387,targeted_by ARO:3000670,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000046,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000066,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000382,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000385,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000456,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000461,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000583,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000584,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000669,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000672,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000673,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000674,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000675,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000677,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000678,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000679,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000680,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000681,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000682','The bacterial 23S rRNA, at the P site of the 50S subunit, has peptidyl transferase activity and is responsible for peptide synthesis and elongation.'),(643,'ARO:3000755','antibiotic sensitive 16S rRNA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000740','part_of ARO:3000728,targeted_by ARO:0000016,targeted_by ARO:3000050,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000003,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000005,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000007,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000012,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000013,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000014,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000021,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000024,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000030,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000035,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000037,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000038,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000039,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000040,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000049,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000051,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000052,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000069,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000119,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000152,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000214,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000528,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000652,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000653,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000654,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000655,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000657,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000658,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000667,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000668,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000700,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000701','The 16S rRNA of the 30S ribosomal subunit helps to stabilize the aminoacyl-tRNAs for pairing with the mRNA codons. Some antibiotics (aminoglycosides) that target the 16S rRNA lead to mRNA misreading as well as premature termination. Other antibiotics (tetracyclines) that target the 16S rRNA prevent incoming charged-tRNAs from binding to the ribosome`s A-site, stopping elongation.'),(644,'ARO:3000756','30S ribosomal subunit P-site','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000728','targeted_by ARO:3000119,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000047,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000130,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000134,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000135,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000136','The P-site of the ribosome binds the peptidyl-tRNA with the growing polypeptide chain. Antibiotics that target the P-site block fMet-tRNA from entering, thus inhibiting peptide elongation.'),(645,'ARO:3000757','50S ribosomal subunit P-site','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000727','targeted_by ARO:0000050,targeted_by ARO:3000079,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000006,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000027,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000057,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000065,targeted_by_drug ARO:0000072,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000145,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000156,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000158,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000176,targeted_by_drug ARO:3000686','The P-site of the ribosome binds the peptidyl-tRNA with the growing polypeptide chain, and is a common target for many antibiotics that inhibit the 50S ribosomal subunit. Some antibiotics (oxazolidinones) block the 50S subunit from interacting with the 30S subunit to prevent the formation of the ribosomal complex. Other antibiotics (thiostrepton) block the 50S subunit from interacting with elongation factors G and Tu (EF-G, Ef-Tu), preventing GTP-dependent reactions of peptidyl transferase, and translocation, respectively. Other antibiotics (macrolides) prevent protein translocation.'),(646,'ARO:3000758','fosmidomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000003','','Fosmidomycin is an inhibitor of 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase, an enzyme in the non-mevalonate pathway for isoprenoid synthesis. It is active against enterobacteria, but not against Gram-positive bacteria or anaerobes.'),(647,'ARO:3000759','fusidic acid','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000003','','Fusidic acid is the only commercially available fusidane, a group of steroid-like antibiotics. It is most active against Gram-positive bacteria, and acts by inhibiting elongation factor G to  block protein synthesis.'),(648,'ARO:3000760','cycloserine','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000003','','Cycloserine is an anti-mycobacterial agent, and is active against enterobacteria, streptococci, M. tuberculosis, Staphylococcus aureus, and many Gram-negative and Gram-positive bacteria. It inhibits cell wall biosynthesis.'),(649,'ARO:3000761','mecillinam','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000008','','Mecillinam is a broad-spectrum beta-lactam antibiotic that was semi-synthetically derived to have a different drug centre, being a 6-alpha-amidinopenicillanate instead of a 6-alpha-acylaminopenicillanate. Contrasting most beta-lactam drugs, mecillinam is most active against Gram-negative bacteria. It binds specifically to penicillin binding protein 2 (PBP2).'),(650,'ARO:3000762','pefloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Pefloxacin is structurally and functionally similar to norfloxacin. It is poorly active against mycobacteria, while anaerobes are resistant.'),(651,'ARO:3000763','antibiotic sensitive embC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000725','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000497','EmbC is an arabinosyltransferase involved in lipoarabinomannan synthesis.'),(652,'ARO:3000764','antibiotic sensitive embA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000725','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000497','EmbA is an arabinosyltransferase that works as a heterodimer with EmbB. It is involved in the synthesis of arabinogalactan, a component of the mycobacterial cell wall.'),(653,'ARO:3000765','antibiotic sensitive embB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000725','targeted_by_drug ARO:3000497','EmbB is an arabinosyltransferase that works as a heterodimer with EmbA. It is involved in the synthesis of arabinogalactan, a component of the mycobacterial cell wall.'),(654,'ARO:3000766','antibiotic sensitive topoisomerase subunit','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000712','','Topoisomerases are responsible for winding and relaxing supercoiled DNA. The subunits of gyrase (gyrA, gyrB) and topoisomerase IV (parC, parE, parY) are targeted by antibiotics.'),(655,'ARO:3000767','avoparcin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000081','','Avoparcin is a glycopeptide antibiotic that is an analog of vancomycin. It was formally used to treat animals, but has since been banned because of its selection for vancomycin-resistant enterococci.'),(656,'ARO:3000768','abeS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010003','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000111','AbeS in an efflux pump of the SMR family of transporters found in Acinetobacter baumannii.'),(657,'ARO:3000769','PatA-PatB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010001','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000036,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000662','PatA-PatB is an efflux protein complex that is associated with fluoroquinolone resistance in Streptococcus pneumoniae. Experiments indicate that PatA and PatB form a heterodimeric transporter.'),(658,'ARO:3000770','AdeABC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000030,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051','AdeABC is an RND multidrug efflux system in Acinetobacter species, notably A. baunmannii. AdeA is a membrane fusion protein, AdeB is the inner membrane transporter, and AdeC is the outer membrane factor. It confers resistance to tigecycline.'),(659,'ARO:3000771','AdeFGH','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051','AdeFGH is a RND multidrug efflux pump expressed in Acinetobacter baumannii. It confers resistance to fluoroquinolone, tetracycline, tigecycline, chloramphenicol, clindamycin, trimethoprim, and sulfamethoxazole.'),(660,'ARO:3000772','AdeIJK','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000000,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000017,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000032,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000169,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000170,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000188,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000385,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3003832','AdeIJK is a RND multidrug efflux pump expressed in Acinetobacter baumannii. It contributes to resistance for beta-lactams, chloramphenicol, tetracycline, erythromycin, lincosamides, fluoroquinolone, fusidic acid, novobiocin, rifampicin, trimethoprim, acridine, pyronine, and safranin.'),(661,'ARO:3000773','CmeABC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000645,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000759','CmeABC is a multidrug efflux pump in Campylobacter jejuni. Its overexpression led to enhanced resistance to ciprofloxacin, norfloxacin, cefotaxime, fusidic acid, and erythromycin. CmeA acts as the periplasmic fusion protein, CmeB is the inner membrane transporter, and CmeC is an outer membrane protein.'),(662,'ARO:3000774','adeA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000770','AdeA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex AdeABC.'),(663,'ARO:3000775','adeB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000770','AdeB is the multidrug transporter of the adeABC efflux system.'),(664,'ARO:3000777','adeF','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000771','AdeF is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex AdeFGH.'),(665,'ARO:3000778','adeG','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000771','AdeG is the inner membrane transporter of the AdeFGH multidrug efflux complex.'),(666,'ARO:3000779','adeH','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000771','AdeH is the outer membrane channel protein of the AdeFGH multidrug efflux complex.'),(667,'ARO:3000780','adeI','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000772','AdeI is the membrane fusion protein of the AdeIJK multidrug efflux complex.'),(668,'ARO:3000781','adeJ','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000772','AdeJ is a RND efflux protein that acts as the inner membrane transporter of the AdeIJK efflux complex. It has 57% identity with E. coli AcrB.'),(669,'ARO:3000782','adeK','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000772','AdeK is the outer membrane factor protein in the adeIJK multidrug efflux complex.'),(670,'ARO:3000783','cmeA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000773','CmeA is the membrane fusion protein of the CmeABC multidrug efflux complex.'),(671,'ARO:3000784','cmeB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000773','CmeB is the inner membrane transporter the CmeABC multidrug efflux complex.'),(672,'ARO:3000785','cmeC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000773','CmeC is the outer membrane channel protein of the CmeABC multidrug efflux complex.'),(673,'ARO:3000786','MdsABC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000004,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000020,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000032,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000044,confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008,confers_resistance_to ARO:3003706,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000385','MdsABC, or GesABC, is a RND-type efflux complex found in Salmonella. In addition to its metal-efflux system, GesABC is also capable of exporting beta-lactams, chloramphenicol, and thiamphenicol. GesB is the inner membrane transporter and is similar to MexF; GesA is the membrane-fusion protein, and GesC is the outer membrane factor.'),(674,'ARO:3000787','MdtABC-TolC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000111','MdtABC-TolC is a multidrug efflux system in Gram-negative bacteria, including E. coli and Salmonella. MdtA is a membrane fusion protein; TolC is the outer membrane channel; MdtBC form a drug transporter. In the absence of MdtB, the MdtAC-TolC has narrower drug specificity, leading to the loss of novobiocin resistance, for example.'),(675,'ARO:3000788','MdtEF-TolC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000011,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000056,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000662','MdtEF-TolC is a multidrug efflux complex in Gram-negative bacteria, including E. coli. MdtE is the membrane fusion protein, MdtF is the inner membrane transporter, while TolC is the outer membrane channel.'),(676,'ARO:3000789','mdsA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000786','MdsA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug and metal efflux complex MdsABC.'),(677,'ARO:3000790','mdsB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000786','MdsB is the inner membrane transporter of the multidrug and metal efflux complex MdsABC. mdsB corresponds to 1 locus in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: mexQ) and 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.'),(678,'ARO:3000791','mdsC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000786','MdsC is the outer membrane channel of the multidrug and metal efflux complex MdsABC.'),(679,'ARO:3000792','mdtA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000787','MdtA is the membrane fusion protein of the multidrug efflux complex mdtABC.'),(680,'ARO:3000793','mdtB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000787','MdtB is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtC to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex.'),(681,'ARO:3000794','mdtC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000787','MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. In the absence of MdtB, MdtC can form a homomultimer complex that results in a functioning efflux complex with a narrower drug specificity. mdtC corresponds to 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: muxC/muxB) and 3 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58.'),(682,'ARO:3000795','mdtE','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000788','MdtE is the membrane fusion protein of the MdtEF multidrug efflux complex. It shares 70% sequence similarity with AcrA.'),(683,'ARO:3000796','mdtF','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000788','MdtF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter for the MdtEF-TolC efflux complex.'),(684,'ARO:3000797','MexCD-OprJ','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000000,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000032,confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000111,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000188,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000385','MexCD-OprJ is a multidrug efflux protein expressed in the Gram-negative Pseudomonas aeruginosa. MexC is the membrane fusion protein; MexD is the inner membrane transporter; and OprJ is the outer membrane channel. MexAB-OprM is associated with resistance to fluoroquinolones, chloramphenicol, and macrolides. MexCD-OprJ is typically quiescent in wild-type cells, with expression following mutation of the nfxB gene that is divergently transcribed from the mexCD-oprJ operon and encodes a repressor of mexCD-oprJ expression. Expression of mexCD–oprJ is controlled by a single known regulator, the NfxB repressor encoded by the nfxB gene, which is transcribed divergently from the efflux genes.'),(685,'ARO:3000798','MexEF-OprN','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000001,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000188,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000385','MexEF-OprN is a multidrug efflux protein expressed in the Gram-negative Pseudomonas aeruginosa. MexE is the membrane fusion protein; MexF is the inner membrane transporter; and OprN is the outer membrane channel. MexEF-OprN is associated with resistance to fluoroquinolones, chloramphenicol, and trimethoprim. Regulation of mexEF-oprN operon expression is multifaceted with the MexT activator being one of the most prominent regulatory proteins. MexEF-OprN is the only positively regulated RND pump of P. aeruginosa.'),(686,'ARO:3000799','MexGHI-OpmD','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010004','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000045,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000662','MexGHI-OpmD is an efflux complex expressed in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. MexG is a membrane protein required for drug export; MexH is the membrane fusion protein; MexI is the inner membrane transporter; and MexJ is the outer membrane channel protein. MexGHI-OpmD confers resistance to vanadium, norfloxacin, and acriflavin.'),(687,'ARO:3000800','MexC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000797,part_of ARO:3004061,part_of ARO:3004062','MexC is the membrane fusion protein of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.'),(688,'ARO:3000801','MexD','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000797,part_of ARO:3004061,part_of ARO:3004062','MexD is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexCD-OprJ complex.'),(689,'ARO:3000802','OprJ','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000797,part_of ARO:3004061,part_of ARO:3004062','OprJ is the outer membrane channel component of the MexCD-OprJ multidrug efflux complex.'),(690,'ARO:3000803','MexE','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000798,part_of ARO:3004066,part_of ARO:3004068,part_of ARO:3004070','MexE is the membrane fusion protein of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.'),(691,'ARO:3000804','MexF','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000798,part_of ARO:3004066,part_of ARO:3004068,part_of ARO:3004070','MexF is the multidrug inner membrane transporter of the MexEF-OprN complex. mexF corresponds to 2 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 (gene name: mexF/mexB) and 4 loci in Pseudomonas aeruginosa LESB58 (gene name: mexD/mexB).'),(692,'ARO:3000805','OprN','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000798,part_of ARO:3004066,part_of ARO:3004068,part_of ARO:3004070','OprN is the outer membrane channel component of the MexEF-OprN multidrug efflux complex.'),(693,'ARO:3000806','MexG','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000799','MexG is a membrane protein required for MexGHI-OpmD efflux activity.'),(694,'ARO:3000807','MexH','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000799','MexH is the membrane fusion protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.'),(695,'ARO:3000808','MexI','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000799','MexI is the inner membrane transporter of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.'),(696,'ARO:3000809','OpmD','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000799','OpmD is the outer membrane channel protein of the efflux complex MexGHI-OpmD.'),(697,'ARO:3000810','mtrC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000369','MtrC is the membrane fusion protein of the MtrCDE multidrug efflux complex.'),(698,'ARO:3000811','mtrD','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000369','MtrD is the inner membrane multidrug transporter of the MtrCDE efflux complex.'),(699,'ARO:3000812','mtrE','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000748','part_of ARO:3000369','MtrE is an outer membrane exporter protein that is part of the MtrCDE multidrug efflux complex.'),(700,'ARO:3000813','MexS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','part_of ARO:3004068,regulates ARO:3000798','MexS is a suppressor of MexT, which is an activator of the multidrug pump MexEF-OprN. Mutations in MexS lead to multidrug resistance.'),(701,'ARO:3000814','MexT','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','part_of ARO:3004066,part_of ARO:3004068,regulates ARO:3000798','MexT is a LysR-type transcriptional activator that positively regulates the expression of MexEF-OprN, OprD, and MexS.'),(702,'ARO:3000815','mgrA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000391,regulates ARO:3000421,regulates ARO:3000565,regulates ARO:3003942','MgrA, also known as NorR, is a regulator for norA, norB, and tet38. It is a positive regulator for norA expression, but is a direct repressor for norB and an indirect repressor of tet38.'),(703,'ARO:3000816','mtrA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000369','MtrA is a transcriptional activator of the MtrCDE multidrug efflux pump of Neisseria gonorrhoeae.'),(704,'ARO:3000817','mtrR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000369,regulates ARO:3003960','MtrR is a repressor of mtrCDE expression. Mutations in mtrR increase multidrug resistance.'),(705,'ARO:3000818','nalC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','part_of ARO:3004051,regulates ARO:3000386','NalC is a repressor of PA3720-PA3719, which are positive regulators of MexAB-OprM. Thus, nalC mutants confer multidrug resistance.'),(706,'ARO:3000819','nalD','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','part_of ARO:3004052,regulates ARO:3000386','NalD is a repressor of MexAB-OprM. Mutations lead to multidrug resistance and MexAB-OprM overexpression.'),(707,'ARO:3000820','NfxB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000797','NfxB is a repressor of the efflux pump mexCD-oprJ and itself (NfxB binds upstream of the nfxB gene and negatively regulates its own expression). Increased expression of MexCD–OprJ brought about by mutations in NfxB.'),(708,'ARO:3000821','phoPQ','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000053,regulates ARO:3000545,regulates ARO:3002985,regulates ARO:3003579','PhoPQ is a two-component regulatory system. phoP is phosphorylated by phoQ at a low [mg2+], activating the repressor. Its part of a two component regulating system that activates the PmrA/B system which has downstream effects, leading to Antimicrobial resistance in many pathogens. In Salmonella, phoP bind to macAB ABC transporter and represses it. In Escherichia coli, phoPQ regulates arnA expression. In Pseudomonas aeruginosa, phoPQ regulates OprH expression. phoPQ have other roles in other species.'),(709,'ARO:3000822','pmrA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000036,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000662','PmrA is a MFS-type efflux pump expressed in Streptococcus pneumoniae that confers low-level resistance to norfloxacin, ciprofloxacin, and acriflavine.'),(710,'ARO:3000823','ramA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000265,regulates ARO:3000384','RamA (resistance antibiotic multiple) is a positive regulator of AcrAB-TolC and leads to high level multidrug resistance in Klebsiella pneumoniae, Salmonella enterica, and Enterobacter aerugenes, increasing the expression of both the mar operon as well as AcrAB. RamA also decreases OmpF expression.'),(711,'ARO:3000824','ramR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000219,ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000384','RamR is a repressor that regulates RamA expression. Mutations lead to the upregulation of AcrAB, which is positively regulated by RamA.'),(712,'ARO:3000825','rob','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000384','robA is a positive regulator for the acrAB efflux genes, and is structurally similar to SoxS and MarA.'),(713,'ARO:3000826','sdiA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000384','SdiA is a cell division regulator that is also a positive regulator of AcrAB only when it`s expressed from a plasmid. When the sdiA gene is on the chromosome, it has no effect on expression of acrAB'),(714,'ARO:3000827','soxRS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000451','regulates ARO:3000384,regulates ARO:3000448,regulates ARO:3000769','SoxRS is a two-component regulator part of the superoxide stress response. It is a positive regulator for many multidrug ef