t is co-expressed with an MBL and controlled by the same promoter region.'),(1082,'ARO:3001206','antibiotic inactivation by sequestration','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0001004','','Inactivation of an antibiotic by formation of a complex, preventing interaction of the antibiotic with its target.'),(1083,'ARO:3001207','gene involved in antibiotic sequestration','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000000','','A gene whose product inactivates an antibiotic by formation of a complex, preventing interaction of the antibiotic with its target.'),(1084,'ARO:3001208','methicillin resistant PBP2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000381,ARO:3003040','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008,part_of ARO:3000268','In methicillin sensitive S. aureus (MSSA), beta-lactams bind to native penicillin-binding proteins (PBPs) and disrupt synthesis of the cell membrane`s peptidoglycan layer. In methicillin resistant S. aureus (MRSA), foreign PBP2a acquired by lateral gene transfer is able to perform peptidoglycan synthesis in the presence of beta-lactams.'),(1085,'ARO:3001209','mecC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001208','','A foreign PBP2a acquired by lateral gene transfer that able to perform peptidoglycan synthesis in the presence of beta-lactams.'),(1086,'ARO:3001214','mdtM','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000045,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000046,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000047,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000385,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000662','Multidrug resistance protein MdtM'),(1087,'ARO:3001215','mdtL','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','','Putative/predicted multidrug resistance protein MdtL (YidY).'),(1088,'ARO:3001216','mdtH','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000023,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000662','Multidrug resistance protein MdtH'),(1089,'ARO:3001218','trimethoprim resistant dihydrofolate reductase dfr','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003425,ARO:3004028','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000171,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000188,derives_from ARO:3000745','Alternative dihydropteroate synthase dfr present on plasmids produces alternate proteins that are less sensitive to trimethoprim from inhibiting its role in folate synthesis, thus conferring trimethoprim resistance.'),(1090,'ARO:3001219','elfamycin antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000003','','Elfamycins are molecules that inhibit bacterial elongation factor Tu (EF-Tu), a key protein which brings aminoacyl-tRNA (aa-tRNA) to the ribosome during protein synthesis. Elfamycins defined by their target (EF-Tu), rather than a conserved chemical backbone. Elfamycins follow two mechanisms to disrupt protein synthesis: 1. kirromycins and enacyloxin fix EF-Tu in the GTP bound conformation and lock EF-Tu onto the ribosome, and 2. pulvomycin and GE2270 cover the binding site of aa-tRNA disallowing EF-Tu from being charged with aa-tRNA. All elfamycins cause increased the affinity of EF-Tu for GTP.'),(1091,'ARO:3001220','factumycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Factumycin is a kirromycin-like antibiotic produced by Kitasatospora setae and Streptomyces strains. Its biosynthetic cluster has been characterized which has interesting acetyl transferase domains in trans, or outside of the polyketide synthase domains. Factumycin has specific, rather than broad spectrum,  antibacterial properties, especially targeting various Acinetobacter baumanii strains.'),(1092,'ARO:3001221','josamycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','A macrolide antibiotic from Streptomyces narbonensis subsp. josamyceticus. The drug has antimicrobial activity against a wide spectrum of pathogens.'),(1093,'ARO:3001222','chalcomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Streptomyces bikiniensis'),(1094,'ARO:3001223','midecamycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Streptomyces mycarofaciens.'),(1095,'ARO:3001224','mycinamicin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Micromonospora griseorubida.'),(1096,'ARO:3001225','megalomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Micromonospora megalomicia.'),(1097,'ARO:3001226','narbomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Streptomyces narbonensis.'),(1098,'ARO:3001227','kitasamycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Kitasamycin is a macrolide antibiotic and is produced by Streptoverticillium kitasatoense. The drug has antimicrobial activity against a wide spectrum of pathogens.'),(1099,'ARO:3001228','carbomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Streptomyces halstedii and Streptomyces thermotolerans.'),(1100,'ARO:3001229','rosaramicin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Micromonospora rosaria.'),(1101,'ARO:3001230','niddamycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Streptomyces caelestis.'),(1102,'ARO:3001231','celesticetin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000017','','Produced by Streptomyces caelestis, which also produces the macrolide niddamycin.'),(1103,'ARO:3001232','methymycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Streptomyces venezuelae ATCC 15439.'),(1104,'ARO:3001233','pikromycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000000','','Produced by Streptomyces venezuelae ATCC 15439.'),(1105,'ARO:3001234','kirromycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Kirromycin, also known as mocimycin, is the representative molecule of its own class of elfamycins which is composed of more than 10 analogs. Kirromycin binds to the domain 1,2 interface of elongation factor Tu. This interaction maintains the EF-Tu*GTP conformation even after GTP is hydrolyzed to GDP. EF-Tu*GDP normally releases aa-tRNA and then exits the ribosome; however, kirromycin*EF-Tu*GDP*aa-tRNA forms a strong complex and remains bound to the ribosome, prohibits translocation of the peptide chain and translation is halted.'),(1106,'ARO:3001235','aurodox','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Aurodox is an elongation factor Tu inhibiting antibiotic. It was first referred to as X-5108. It is produced by Streptomyces goldiniensis var. goldiniensis and is active primarily against gram-positive bacteria.'),(1107,'ARO:3001236','efrotomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Efrotomycin is produced by Streptomyces lactamodurans NRRL 3802. This kirromycin-like antibiotic is used in animal agriculture, especially in the production of swine. Generally gram negative bacteria are susceptible to efrotomycin, while gram positive bacteria are resistant.'),(1108,'ARO:3001237','GE2270A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001309','','GE2270A is the model molecule of cyclic thiazolyl peptide elfamycins. \nGE2270A is produced by Planobispora rosea. Biosynthesis of the molecule has been shown to originate as a ribosomally synthesized peptide that undergoes significant post-translational modification. Clinical use of cyclic thiazolyl peptides is hindered by their low water solubility and bioavailability.'),(1109,'ARO:3001242','enacyloxin IIa','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001219','','Enacyloxin IIa is structurally distinct but acts in a similar mechanism to kirromycin-like elfamycins. It prohibits the transfer of the amino acid at the A site to the elongating peptide chain. It is most likely that the mechanism of action is that EF-Tu*GDP is locked in the EF-Tu*GTP form, and EF-Tu*GDP*aa-tRNA is immobilized on the ribosome. It is an open question whether enacyloxin IIa actually belongs to the kirromycin-like group of elfamycins due to their high similarity.'),(1110,'ARO:3001246','kirrothricin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Kirrothricin is produced by Streptomyces cinnamoneus and is structurally related to kirromycin, aurodox, heneicomycin and shares a similar spectrum of antibacterial activity.'),(1111,'ARO:3001247','azimycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Azimycin is produced by Streptomyces diastatochromogenes ATCC 31013.'),(1112,'ARO:3001248','dihydromocimycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Dihydromocimycin is produced by Streptomyces ramocissimus CBS190.69.'),(1113,'ARO:3001249','phenelfamycin A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Phenelfamycin A was isolated from two environmental isolates called AB999F-80 and AB1047T-33. They were both identified as Streptomyces violaceoniger strains. Both these strains were found to produce phenelfamycins A-F and unphenelfamycin. Phenelfamycin A has a monosaccaride moeity and is isomeric with phenelfamycin B. All phenelfamycins were selected due to their activity against anaerobic bacteria, especially Clostridioides difficile.'),(1114,'ARO:3001250','phenelfamycin B','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Phenelfamycin B was isolated from two environmental isolates called AB999F-80 and AB1047T-33. They were both identified as Streptomyces violaceoniger strains. Both these strains were found to produce phenelfamycins A-F and unphenelfamycin. Phenelfamycin B has a monosaccaride moeity and is isomeric with phenelfamycin A. All phenelfamycins were selected due to their activity against anaerobic bacteria, especially Clostridioides difficile.'),(1115,'ARO:3001251','phenelfamycin C','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Phenelfamycin C was isolated from two environmental isolates called AB999F-80 and AB1047T-33. They were both identified as Streptomyces violaceoniger strains. Both these strains were found to produce phenelfamycins A-F and unphenelfamycin. Phenelfamycin C has a disaccaride moeity and is isomeric with phenelfamycin D. All phenelfamycins were selected due to their activity against anaerobic bacteria, especially Clostridioides difficile.'),(1116,'ARO:3001252','phenelfamycin D','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Phenelfamycin D was isolated from two environmental isolates called AB999F-80 and AB1047T-33. They were both identified as Streptomyces violaceoniger strains. Both these strains were found to produce phenelfamycins A-F and unphenelfamycin. Phenelfamycin D has a disaccaride moeity and is isomeric with phenelfamycin C. All phenelfamycins were selected due to their activity against anaerobic bacteria, especially Clostridioides difficile.'),(1117,'ARO:3001253','phenelfamycin E','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Phenelfamycin E was isolated from two environmental isolates called AB999F-80 and AB1047T-33. They were both identified as Streptomyces violaceoniger strains. Both these strains were found to produce phenelfamycins A-F and unphenelfamycin. Phenelfamycin E has a trisaccaride moeity and is isomeric with phenelfamycin F. All phenelfamycins were selected due to their activity against anaerobic bacteria, especially Clostridioides difficile. Phenelfamycin E and F are the most potent of the phenelfamycins.'),(1118,'ARO:3001256','phenelfamycin F','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Phenelfamycin F was isolated from two environmental isolates called AB999F-80 and AB1047T-33. They were both identified as Streptomyces violaceoniger strains. Both these strains were found to produce phenelfamycins A-F and unphenelfamycin. Phenelfamycin F has a trisaccaride moeity and is isomeric with phenelfamycin E. All phenelfamycins were selected due to their activity against anaerobic bacteria, especially Clostridioides difficile. Phenelfamycin E and F are the most potent of the phenelfamycins.'),(1119,'ARO:3001257','unphenelfamycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Unphenelfamycin was isolated from two environmental isolates called AB999F-80 and AB1047T-33. They were both identified as Streptomyces violaceoniger strains. Both these strains were found to produce phenelfamycins A-F and unphenelfamycin. Unphenelfamycin has a monosaccaride moeity and lacks the  phenacetyl moeity present in the other phenelfamycins. All phenelfamycins were selected due to their activity against anaerobic bacteria, especially Clostridioides difficile.'),(1120,'ARO:3001258','L-681,217','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','L-681217 is a kirromycin-like antibiotic produced by Streptomyces cattleya. Its biosynthetic gene cluster is characterized.'),(1121,'ARO:3001259','GE37468','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001309','','GE37468 is a thiazolyl peptide produced by Streptomyces ATCC 55365. GE37468 is produced by post-transcription modification of a ribosomally synthesized preprotein, of which the biosynthetic gene cluster has been elucidated.'),(1122,'ARO:3001260','amythiamicin A','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001309','','Amythiamicin A is a cyclic thiazolyl peptide antibiotic with a structure similar to GE2270A. Amythiamicin B, C, and D also exist, but are not discussed further here. Amythiamicin A was shown to have the highest activity in cell free protein synthesis assays.'),(1123,'ARO:3001264','heneicomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3001310','','Heneicomycin is a kirromycin-like antibiotic, isolated from Streptomyces filipinensis. It is structurally related to kirromycin, aurodox and efrotomycin.'),(1124,'ARO:3001265','Erm(30)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000560','','Erm(30) confers a MLSb resistant phenotype. Along with erm(31), these genes are responsible for self-resistance in the pikromycin/narbomycin/methymycin/neomethymycin producer, Streptomyces venezuelae.'),(1125,'ARO:3001294','verdamicin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','A gentamicin-group aminoglycoside isolated from Micromonospora.'),(1126,'ARO:3001295','vertilimicin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','A semisynthetic genamicin-group aminoglycoside, derived from verdamicin.'),(1127,'ARO:3001296','kasugamycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000016','','An unusual aminoglycoside because the cyclitol ring is not amino substituted; it was discovered as a fermentation product of Streptomyces kasugaensis.'),(1128,'ARO:3001298','non-erm 23S ribosomal RNA methyltransferase (G748)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000315,ARO:3004274','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000000,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000017','Non-erm 23S ribosomal RNA methyltransferases modify guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering) to confer resistance to some macrolides and lincosamides'),(1129,'ARO:3001299','tlrB conferring tylosin resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000492,ARO:3001298','','TlrB is a methyltransferase found in Streptomyces fradiae and confers resistance to mycinamicin, tylosin and lincosamides. Specifically, this enzyme adds a methyl group to guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering). TlrB is found in the tylosin biosynthetic cluster and is one mechanism by which S. fradiae protects itself from self-destruction when producing this macrolide.'),(1130,'ARO:3001300','myrA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000492,ARO:3001298','','myrA is a methyltransferase found in Micromonospora griseorubida and confers resistance to mycinamicin, tylosin and lincosamides. Specifically, this enzyme adds a methyl group to guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering) of 23S ribosomal RNA. MyrA is found in the mycinamicin biosynthetic cluster and is one mechanism by which M. griseorubida protects itself from self-destruction when producing this macrolide.'),(1131,'ARO:3001301','RlmA(II)','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000492,ARO:3001298','','RlmA(II) is a methyltransferase found in Streptococcus pneumoniae and confers resistance to mycinamicin, tylosin and lincosamides. Specifically, this enzyme adds a methyl group to guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering) of 23S ribosomal RNA.'),(1132,'ARO:3001302','chrB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000492,ARO:3001298','','ChrB is a methyltransferase found in Streptomyces bikiniensis and confers resistance to chalcomycin, mycinamicin, tylosin and lincosamides. Specifically, this enzyme adds a methyl group to guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering). chrB is found in the chalcomycin biosynthetic cluster and is responsible for self-resistance in S. bikiniensis.'),(1133,'ARO:3001303','ErmO-srmA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000560','','ErmO (gene srmA) is a methyltransferase found in the spiramycin producer Streptomyces ambofaciens. Like other Erm enzymes, it catalyzes the methylation of A2058 of the 23S ribosomal RNA. Specifically, this enzyme transfers only one methyl group. The gene is responsible for self-resistance to spiramycin.'),(1134,'ARO:3001304','ErmS','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000560','','ErmS is a methyltransferase found in the tylosin producer Streptomyces fradiae. Like other Erm enzymes, it catalyzes the methylation of A2058 of the 23S ribosomal RNA. Specifically, this enzyme transfers two methyl groups. The gene is found within the tylosin biosynthetic cluster and is responsible for self-resistance'),(1135,'ARO:3001305','ErmU','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000560','','ErmU is a methyltransferase found in the lincomycin producer Streptomyces lincolnensis. Like other Erm enzymes, it catalyzes the methylation of A2058 of the 23S ribosomal RNA. Specifically, this enzyme transfers only one methyl group. The gene is found in the lincomycin biosynthetic cluster and is responsible for self-resistance.'),(1136,'ARO:3001306','ErmW','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000560','','ErmW is a methyltransferase found in the mycinamicin producer Micromonospora griseorubida. Like other Erm enzymes, it catalyzes the methylation of A2058 of the 23S ribosomal RNA. The gene is found within the mycinamicin biosynthetic cluster and is responsible for self-resistance.'),(1137,'ARO:3001307','vgbA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000376','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000583,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000584,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000675,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000677,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000678,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000679,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000680,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000681,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000682','vgbA inactivates streptogramin B-type antibiotics by linearizing the lactone ring on the ester bond using an elimination mechanism, thus conferring resistance to these compounds.'),(1138,'ARO:3001308','vgbB','antibiotic_