e to edeine'),(2948,'ARO:3003231','Lipid II','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000721','targeted_by_drug ARO:3003241','Precursor molecule during the synthesis of bacterial cell wall. Lipid II anchors itself onto the cell and it`s disaccharide-peptide subunit is used in PG polymer assembly by peptidoglycan glycosyltransferases. Due to it`s importance in cell wall synthesis, it is the target of antibiotics.'),(2949,'ARO:3003232','Lipid III','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000721','targeted_by_drug ARO:3003241','Lipid III is the precursor to the wall teichoic acid. It`s inhibition leads to bacterial death as teichoic acid is required to anchor autolysins which control the hydrolysis of peptidoglycan cell wall.'),(2950,'ARO:3003236','Mycobacteroides abscessus 16S rRNA mutation conferring resistance to kanamycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003666','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000049','Point mutations in the 16S rRNA of Mycobacteroides abscessus conferring resistance to kanamycin'),(2951,'ARO:3003237','Mycobacteroides abscessus 16S rRNA mutation conferring resistance to tobramycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003666','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000052','Point mutations in the 16S rRNA of Mycobacteroides abscessus conferring resistance to tobramycin'),(2952,'ARO:3003238','Mycobacteroides abscessus 16S rRNA mutation conferring resistance to neomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003666','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000005','Point mutations in the 16S rRNA of Mycobacteroides abscessus conferring resistance to neomycin'),(2953,'ARO:3003239','Mycobacteroides abscessus 16S rRNA mutation conferring resistance to amikacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003666','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000013','Point mutations in the 16S rRNA of Mycobacteroides abscessus conferring resistance to amikacin'),(2954,'ARO:3003240','Mycobacteroides abscessus 16S rRNA mutation conferring resistance to gentamicin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003666','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0