nce','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000045,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000047','MdtNOP is a MFS efflux pump protein found in E. coli. The deletion of mdtP from strain W3110 resulted in increased susceptibility to acriflavin, puromycin, and tetraphenylarsonium chloride. An E. coli mdtN null mutant is more sensitive to sulfur drugs than wild type'),(3642,'ARO:3004102','kamB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004272','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000005,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000037,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000049','Methyltransferase enzyme first described in Streptoalloteichus tenebrarius. Confers resistance to aminoglycoside antibiotics (esp. apramycin) through methylation of the 16S rRNA at A1408, thereby modifying the antibiotic target.'),(3643,'ARO:3004103','QepA2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0010002','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000036,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000074,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000662','QepA2 is a plasmid-mediated quinolone resistance pump found in an Escherichia coli isolate from France'),(3644,'ARO:3004104','TMB beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000568','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000020,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000032,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000044','TMB-1, the first known member of the Tripoli metallo-beta-lactamase family (TMB) was isolated from Achromobacter xylosoxidans in a Tripoli central hospital. TMB-1 was located on a class 1 integron and is a chromosomally-encoded beta-lactamase capable of hydrolyzing multiple antibiotics.'),(3645,'ARO:3004105','TMB-1','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004104','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000060','TMB-1 is a TMB metallo-beta-lactamase found in Achromobacter sp.'),(3646,'ARO:3004106','TMB-2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004104','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000060','TMB-2 is a TMB metallo-beta-lactamase found in Acinetobacter sp.'),(3647,'ARO:3004107','Pseudomonas aeruginosa soxR','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000836','regulates ARO:3000799','SoxR is a redox-sensitive transcriptional activator that induces expression of a small regulon that includes the RND efflux pump-encoding operon mexGHI-opmD. SoxR was shown to be activated by pyocyanin.'),(3648,'ARO:3004108','Enterobacter cloacae rob','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000825','','rob is a positive regulator for the acrAB efflux genes, and is structurally similar to SoxS and MarA.'),(3649,'ARO:3004109','Escherichia coli rob','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000825','','rob is a positive regulator for the acrAB efflux genes, and is structurally similar to SoxS and MarA.'),(3650,'ARO:3004110','MCR-2.1','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004268','','MCR-2 is a plasmid-borne phosphoethanolamine transferase that interferes with binding of colistin to the cell membrane via addition of phosphoethanolamine to lipid A, resulting in reduction of the negative charge of the cell membrane. Originally identified in a Belgian sample of Escherichia coli by Xavier et al, (2016).'),(3651,'ARO:3004111','FosA6','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000133','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000025','fosA6 is a plasmid-encoded enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Escherichia coli by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule.'),(3652,'ARO:3004112','phosphoethanolamine transferase conferring colistin resistance','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3002984,ARO:3003580','','This group of enzymes catalyzes the addition of a phosphoethanolamine group to another molecule. The addition of this moiety to lipid A in bacterial species is often associated with polymyxin (otherwise known as colistin) resistance.'),(3653,'ARO:3004113','FosA7','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000133','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000025','fosA7 is an enzyme that confers resistance to fosfomycin in Escherichia coli by breaking the epoxide ring of the molecule.'),(3654,'ARO:3004114','porin OmpC','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004281','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000058,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3004129','In the presence of antibiotic stress, there is a coupled down-regulation of the porin OmpC with the OmpF.  Mutants both lacking both OmpC and OmpF proteins are resistant to cephaloridine and cefazolin. Analyses of genes involved in the increased resistance to tetracycline suggest that the up-regulation of efflux pump genes is accompanied by a decrease of OmpF and OmpC synthesis. Homologs of OmpC have been identified in Escherichia coli, Salmonella enterica, Klebsiella aerogenes and Serratia marcescens.'),(3655,'ARO:3004115','nitroimidazole antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000003','','Nitroimidazoles are a group of drugs that have both antiprotozoal and antibacterial activity, classified with respect to the location of the nitro functional group.'),(3656,'ARO:3004116','nitrofuran antibiotic','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:1000003','','Nitrofurans are chemotherapeutic agents with antibacterial and antiprotozoal activity.'),(3657,'ARO:3004117','Vibrio cholerae OmpU','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004282','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3004121','A ToxR-Regulated outer membrane porin. In Vibrio cholerae, ToxR controls resistance to P2 (a BPI-derived antimicrobial peptide) by regulating the production of OmpU. OmpU also confers resistance to polymyxin B sulfate.'),(3658,'ARO:3004118','Vibrio cholerae OmpT','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004282','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3004121','A ToxR negatively regulated outer membrane porin. In Vibrio cholerae, ToxR controls resistance to P2 (a BPI-derived antimicrobial peptide) by regulating the production of OmpT, especially in the absence of OmpU.'),(3659,'ARO:3004120','CBP C1-aminomethylene vancomycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000081','','CBP C1-aminomethylene vancomycin is a synthetic vancomycin derivative which exhibits multiple synergistic mechanisms of action, allowing it to effectively inhibit otherwise-glycopeptide resistant Gram-positive bacteria (notably those with functioning VanA clusters).'),(3660,'ARO:3004121','BPI','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000053','','Bactericidal/permeability-increasing (BPI) protein is a member of a new generation of proteins known as super-antibiotics that are implicated as endotoxin neutralising agents. The potent (nM) cytotoxicity of BPI is limited to gram-negative bacteria (GNB), reflecting the high affinity (<10 nM) of BPI for bacterial lipopolysaccharides (LPS). Binding of BPI to live bacteria via LPS causes immediate growth arrest, actual killing coincides with later damage to the inner membrane.'),(3661,'ARO:3004122','Klebsiella pneumoniae OmpK37','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004281','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000008,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000645','Klebsiella pneumoniae outer membrane porin protein. Is preferentially detected in porin-deficient strains. Functional characterization of this new porin revealed a narrower pore than those of porins OmpK35 and OmpK36, which did not allow penetration by certain β-lactams. Also, when a resistant strain expresses porin OmpK37 is less susceptible to cefotaxime and cefoxitin than when it is expressing either OmpK36 or OmpK35.'),(3662,'ARO:3004123','Burkholderia pseudomallei Omp38','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004281','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000008,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000060,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000170,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000632','Heterologous expression of Burkholderia pseudomallei Omp38 (BpsOmp38) in Omp-deficient E. coli host cells lowers their permeability and in consequence, their antimicrobial susceptibility to penicillin G, cefoxitin, ceftazidime and imipenem.'),(3663,'ARO:3004124','Moraxella catarrhalis M35','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003768,ARO:3004281','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000064','The outer membrane protein M35 of Moraxella catarrhalis is an antigenically conserved porin. Down-regulation of M35 significantly increases the MICs of aminopenicillins, specifically amoxicillin.'),(3664,'ARO:3004125','23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to macrolide antibiotics','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000315,ARO:3000336','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000000','Nucleotide point mutations in the 23S rRNA subunit may confer resistance to macrolide antibiotics.'),(3665,'ARO:3004126','Escherichia coli LamB','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003768,ARO:3004279','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000036,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000528,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000661,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3004130','LamB is a negative regulator for antibiotic resistance, it serves as a porin to influx antibiotic. When down-regulated, it increases resistance to chlortetracycline, ciprofloxacin, balofloxacin and nalidixic acid. It also interacts with Odp1, an energy metabolic enzyme, creating a complex that decreases in antibiotic-resistant strains.'),(3666,'ARO:3004127','Escherichia coli mipA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003768,ARO:3004280','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000040,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000049,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000661','MltA-interacting protein (mipA), is an antibiotic resistance-related outer membrane protein. Deletion of mipA increases kanamycin, nalidixic acid and streptomycin resistance.'),(3667,'ARO:3004128','Serratia marcescens Omp1','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3003768,ARO:3004281','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000008,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000036,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000051,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000062,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000385,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000645,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3004017','Omp1 is an outer membrane porin that confers resistance by absence in S. marcescens.  Knockout, deletion or other inhibition of the omp1 gene confers resistance to certain beta-lactamase antibiotics - including Cefoxitin, Ceftriaxone, Cefotaxime, and Moxalactam - as well as Ciprofloxacin, Tetracycline, and Chloramphenicol, by preventing passage of the antibiotic into the cell.'),(3668,'ARO:3004129','cephaloridine','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000032','','Cephaloridine is a semisynthetic, broad-spectrum, first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity. Cephaloridine binds to and inactivates penicillin-binding proteins (PBPs) located on the inner membrane of the bacterial cell wall. PBPs are enzymes involved in the terminal stages of assembling the bacterial cell wall and in reshaping the cell wall during growth and division. Inactivation of PBPs interferes with the cross-linkage of peptidoglycan chains necessary for bacterial cell wall strength and rigidity. This results in the weakening of the bacterial cell wall and causes cell lysis.'),(3669,'ARO:3004130','balofloxacin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:0000001','','Balofloxacin is an 8-methoxy fluoroquinolone antibiotic. It shows potent bactericidal activity and inhibits the supercoiling activity of DNA gyrase of S. aureus, E. coli, and P. aeruginosa.'),(3670,'ARO:3004131','Escherichia coli 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to erythromycin and telithromycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004125','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006,confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000057','Point mutation in the 23S rRNA of Escherichia coli shown clinically to confer resistance to the macrolide-class antibiotics erythromycin and telithromycin.'),(3671,'ARO:3004132','Chlamydomonas reinhardtii 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to erythromycin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004125','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:0000006','Point mutation in 23S rRNA of C. reinhardtii chloroplast shown clinically to confer resistance to Erythromycin, a macrolide antibiotic.'),(3672,'ARO:3004133','Brachyspira hyodysenteriae 23S rRNA with mutation conferring resistance to tylosin','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004125','confers_resistance_to_drug ARO:3000145','Point mutation in B. hyodysenteriae 23S rRNA shown to confer resistance to tylosin and erythromycin'),(3673,'ARO:3004134','Helicobacter pylori 23S rR