bility to hydrolyze cephalosporin.'),(3726,'ARO:3004193','Sed beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000078','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000032,confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008','Sed beta-lactamases are Class A beta-lactamases that are capable of hydrolyzing benzypenicillin, cephalothin, and cloxacillin.'),(3727,'ARO:3004194','MCR-1.2','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004268','evolutionary_variant_of ARO:3003689','A plasmid-borne novel MCR-1 functional variant detected in a Klebsiella pneumoniae isolate collected from a rectal swab in Italy. MCR-1.2 differs from MCR-1 by a single amino acid substitution from Glutamine to Leucine at position 3 in the N-terminal region. Described by DiPilato et al. 2016'),(3728,'ARO:3004195','NmcA beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000078','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000020','nmcA beta-lactamases are chromosomal-encoded Class A beta-lactamases first isolated from Enterobacter cloacae, specifically a clinical strain known as NOR-1. nmcA beta-lactamases have been shown to hydrolyze carbapenems.'),(3729,'ARO:3004196','VCC beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000078','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000004,confers_resistance_to ARO:0000020,confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008','VCC beta-lactamases are Class A beta-lactamases.'),(3730,'ARO:3004197','blaZ beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000078','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008','blaZ beta-lactamases are Class A beta-lactamases. These beta-lactamases are responsible for penicillin resistance in Staphylococcus aureus.'),(3731,'ARO:3004198','R39 beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000078','confers_resistance_to ARO:3000008','R39 beta-lactamases are Class A beta-lactamases encoded in Actinomadura R39 with the ability to hydrolyze penicillins.'),(3732,'ARO:3004199','CepS beta-lactamase','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3000076','confers_resistance_to ARO:0000032','CepS beta-lactamases are Class C beta-lactamases capable of hydrolyzing cephalosporin.'),(3733