004440','','A bacterial strain is said to be susceptible to a given antibiotic when it is inhibited in vitro by a concentration of a drug that is associated with a high likelihood of therapeutic success'),(3833,'ARO:3004303','nonsusceptible antimicrobial phenotype','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004440','','A bacterial strain is said to be nonsusceptible to a given antibiotic drug if it demonstrates either an intermediate or resistant phenotype when exposed to a concentration of a drug that is associated with a high likelihood of therapeutic failure, i.e. if the bacterial strain is not susceptible to the antibiotic drug but not necessarily totally resistant under all conditions.'),(3834,'ARO:3004304','susceptible dose dependent antimicrobial phenotype','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004440','','A bacterial strain is said to be susceptible-dose dependent (SDD) to a given antibiotic when growth is inhibited with a high likelihood of therapeutic success, but when multiple approved dosing options exist. When a higher or more frequent dose is used, the predicted therapeutic result is the same as for susceptible individuals.'),(3835,'ARO:3004305','multidrug resistance antimicrobial phenotype','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004299','','Multidrug-resistant organisms are defined as bacterial strains that have become resistant to multiple classes of antibacterial drugs or other agents. The phenotype of these organisms is defined by the spectrum of antibiotic drug classes to which that organism is resistant. Often, these organisms are susceptible to a narrow range of available drugs, making treatment difficult and urgent.'),(3836,'ARO:3004306','methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004305','','Any strain of Staphylococcus aureus that has tested resistant (R) to at least one of methicillin, oxacillin or cefoxitin by standard susceptibility testing methods.'),(3837,'ARO:3004307','Linezolid-resistant MRSA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004306','','Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus that has additionally tested resistant to the antibiotic drug linezolid'),(3838,'ARO:3004308','Fluoroquinolone-resistant MRSA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004306','','Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus that has additionally tested resistant to the fluoroquinolone antibiotics ciprofloxacin and/or levofloxacin'),(3839,'ARO:3004309','Vancomycin-intermediate MRSA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004306','','Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus that has additionally tested intermediate to vancomycin antibiotics.'),(3840,'ARO:3004310','Daptomycin-resistant MRSA','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004306','','Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus that has additionally tested non-susceptible (NS, resistant or intermediate) to daptomycin antibiotics'),(3841,'ARO:3004311','carbapenem-resistant Acinetobacter','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004305','','Any strain of Acinetobacter spp. that has tested either Intermediate or Resistant to at least one of the following carbapenem-class antibiotics by standard testing using approved breakpoints: imipenem, meropenem, doripenem'),(3842,'ARO:3004312','multidrug-resistant Acinetobacter','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004305','','Any strain of an Acinetobacter spp. that has either tested Intermediate or Resistant to at least one antibiotic drug in at least 3 of the 6 following categories: 1) Extended-spectrum cephalosporins, 2) Fluoroquinolone, 3) Aminoglycosides, 4) Carbapenems, 5) Piperacillin group, and 6) Ampicillin/sulbactam'),(3843,'ARO:3004313','carbapenem-resistant Escherichia coli','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004305','','Any strain of E. coli that has tested resistant to one of the following carbapenem antibiotics: imipenem, meropenem, doripenem, ertapenem.'),(3844,'ARO:3004314','extended-spectrum cephalosporin-resistant Escherichia coli','antibiotic_resistance','ARO:3004305','','Any E.coli that has tested resistant (R) to at least one of the following: ceftriaxone, 